<div class="expanded">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="pclose" src="../images/clear.gif">Our Business:</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">Global Markets Operations/Middle Office group (GMO &amp;MO) provides controlled and cost effective post trade processes in support of our front office businesses.</p>
<p class="bac">Our Middle Office group delivers control functions responsible for providing assurance over data and processes used to record risk, P/L, balance sheet and financial results. There are five core GMO functions that are critical in ensuring business process control: Development, Trade Control/Event Management, P &amp;L substantiation, Balance Sheet Substantiation, and Oversight  &amp; Risk Management.</p>
<p class="bac">Our Global Markets Operations group execute a number of core processes that range from confirmations, client services trade processes, settlements and custody.</p>
<p class="bac">With approximately 20 million transactions per day, we operate to ensure global consistency of processes and strong global and local supervision.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Overview:</h2>
<div>
<p class="bac">Your role could be within either the Middle office or Operations function depending on your skill set and passion.</p>
<p class="bac nobr">Middle Office roles could range from:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Balance sheet reconciliation and monitoring of suspense accounts including investigation and resolution of exceptions to ongoing trade maintenance</li>
	<li>Investigation and resolve pre and post cash settlement discrepancies and non-receipts</li>
	<li>Working with Traders to explain their P &amp;L</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac nobr">Global Markets Operations day to day roles and responsibilities include:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Providing confirmations on transactions</li>
	<li>Dealing with client queries</li>
	<li>Monitoring trade activity and resolving exceptions for Derivatives, FX and Futures and options business</li>
	<li>Delivering trading, sales and syndicate support to the trade desk for Global Markets and Corporate Treasury</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Training:</h2>
<div>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>One week induction and training programme with classroom instruction</li>
	<li>Summer Senior Speaker Series, featuring global  &amp; divisional presentations by top executives</li>
	<li>Opportunities to interact with senior bankers and network with peers</li>
	<li>Constructive feedback sessions through performance evaluations</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif">Qualifications:</h2>
<div>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Applications are accepted from a diverse range of degree disciplines such as the arts and humanities, as well as numerically focused subjects such as economics and mathematics</li>
	<li>Strong A-level grades and on track for a minimum 2:1 degree (or equivalent)</li>
	<li>Fluency in English is essential</li>
	<li>You&#39;ll need to demonstrate drive, innovation and a genuine interest in the financial markets</li>
	<li>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills as well as team-work and a willingness to accept responsibility are key qualities, as is the ability to work in a fast-paced environment, multi-task and interact with a variety of people</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

